---
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta
      name="description"
      content="Agent Doctor checks whether a repository is ready for coding agents."
    />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.svg" type="image/svg+xml" />
    <title>Agent Doctor</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="site-header">
      <a class="brand" href="#top" aria-label="Agent Doctor home">
        <span class="brand-mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        Agent Doctor
      </a>
      <nav class="site-nav" aria-label="Primary navigation">
        <a href="#workflow">Workflow</a>
        <a href="#checks">Checks</a>
        <a href="#install">Install</a>
      </nav>
    </header>

    <main id="top">
      <section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-title">
        <canvas id="ascii-canvas" aria-hidden="true"></canvas>
        <div class="hero-content">
          <p class="eyebrow">Repository readiness for coding agents</p>
          <h1 id="hero-title">Agent Doctor</h1>
          <p class="hero-lede">
            Check whether a project has the context, commands, safety files, and agent tooling it
            needs before you delegate work to Codex, Claude Code, OpenCode, Cursor, or Windsurf.
          </p>
          <div class="hero-actions" aria-label="Primary actions">
            <a class="button button-primary" href="#install">Run the CLI</a>
            <a class="button button-secondary" href="#preview">See output</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero-terminal" id="preview" aria-label="Agent Doctor scan output preview">
          <div class="terminal-top" aria-hidden="true">
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
            <span></span>
          </div>
          <pre><code>$ npx agent-doctor scan
.. Scanning repository...

Agent readiness
  Score: 100/100 ██████████
  Status: Ready

Tool use
  ✓ Codex: ready AGENTS.md, .agents
  - Claude Code: missing
  - OpenCode: missing

Next steps
  - This repository is ready for coding agents.</code></pre>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="principles" aria-label="MVP principles">
        <div>
          <strong>No API keys</strong>
          <span>Agent Doctor runs locally and does not call a model provider.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>No risky fixes</strong>
          <span>It diagnoses, writes safe base files, and creates a prescription.</span>
        </div>
        <div>
          <strong>Your agent executes</strong>
          <span>Use the generated instructions with the coding agent you already trust.</span>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section section-split" id="workflow">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Workflow</p>
          <h2>Diagnose, initialize, prescribe.</h2>
        </div>
        <ol class="workflow-list">
          <li>
            <span>scan</span>
            <p>Read the repository and score its readiness without modifying files.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>init</span>
            <p>Create missing base files such as AGENTS.md and .env.example without overwrites.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span>prescribe</span>
            <p>Generate a focused prompt that tells your coding agent what to fix next.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <section class="section" id="checks">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Checks</p>
          <h2>Signals that reduce agent guesswork.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="check-grid">
          <article>
            <span>01</span>
            <h3>Context</h3>
            <p>README, AGENTS.md, architecture notes, safety rules, and environment examples.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>02</span>
            <h3>Commands</h3>
            <p>Development, build, test, lint, and format scripts that make verification clear.</p>
          </article>
          <article>
            <span>03</span>
            <h3>Agent tools</h3>
            <p>Codex, Claude Code, OpenCode, Cursor, Windsurf, and local skill directories.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section proof-section">
        <div class="section-heading">
          <p class="eyebrow">Output</p>
          <h2>A copyable diagnosis for the next agent run.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="output-grid">
          <pre><code>Found
  ✓ README.md
  ✓ package.json
  ✓ Git repository

Missing
  - AGENTS.md
  - .env.example
  - test script

Prescription
  .agent-doctor/prescription.md</code></pre>
          <p>
            Agent Doctor does not pretend to be the agent. It prepares the repo so the next agent
            has fewer assumptions to make and a clear verification path to follow.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="install" id="install" aria-labelledby="install-title">
        <div>
          <p class="eyebrow">Install</p>
          <h2 id="install-title">Run it from any repository.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="command-row">
          <code>npx agent-doctor scan</code>
          <a class="button button-primary" href="https://github.com/carloss765/agent-doctor">
            View GitHub
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="site-footer">
      <span>Agent Doctor</span>
      <span>Open source repository readiness for coding agents.</span>
    </footer>

    <script>
      import "../scripts/ascii-canvas";
    </script>
  </body>
</html>
